cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.THEORY, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents a dynamic semantics for incomplete functional programs and discusses the implementation of these ideas into the Hazel programming environment. This falls under the domain of programming languages. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses editor services that can help the programmer develop and confirm their mental model of the behavior of the complete portions of the program. This falls under the domain of software engineering. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses contextual modal type theory to supply a logical basis for hole closures. This falls under the domain of logic in computer science. 
4. cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science): The paper develops a formal semantics for incomplete functional programs and proves type safety. This falls under the domain of theoretical computer science. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the implementation of a live programming environment with rich dynamic feedback, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction.
